Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Declutter reorder card: one reason, one primary action,
 progressive disclosure
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Wave 1 of the UI design system. The follow-up card stacked four coloured
reason-boxes (new-customer, scheduled, history, NBA) then five buttons then a
log row — everything shouting at once.

Rebuilt to the rules:
- One reason line (the NBA), coloured only when urgent; everything else calm.
- New-customer / scheduled / history collapse into a single muted context line.
- One primary action (the recommended channel — Call or ✨ Message), with the
  alternatives shrunk to icon buttons.
- The outcome log moves behind a tap (progressive disclosure), still clearly
  marked "required to mark done".

All handlers, data attributes, AI/feedback/plan integration preserved.
Verified by rendering real cards in a headless browser: no errors, both the
Call-primary and Message-primary variants render cleanly.
